  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">URGENT MEDICAL SUPPORT NEEDED IN THE UKRAINE CRISIS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CA will provide &#xA3;2m for purchase and delivery of c. 10,000 kits for MOH in Ukraine and other urgent medical supplies including Baby Incubators, Oxygen Concentrators, and Thermal Blankets
On the morning of 24th February 2022, Russia launched a large-scale invasion of Ukraine. Infrastructure has suffered severe damage. Constant power outages threaten critical hospital services, and vital medical supplies are running low. The ongoing Omicron surge of COVID-19 is also complicating the already-difficult health response in Ukraine. Exacerbating this is the persistent risk of ambulances and health personnel being caught in the crossfire and sustaining war-related life-threatening injuries.
Since the start of the attack, the Ministry of Health of Ukraine has constantly communicated with Crown Agents, sharing details of the medical equipment they require. Within the last 24 hours, the Ministry has approached Crown Agents with an urgent request for 50,000 Individual First Aid Kits which can provide life-saving treatment during the bombardment of civilian areas.</narrative>
  </description>
